President Biden addressed a gathering at The St. Regis Washington, D.C., expressing his gratitude to Native American voters for their support in the 2020 election. He emphasized the importance of the Native American community in preserving the nation's heritage and credited them for his victory. The President highlighted his administration's efforts to strengthen the nation-to-nation relationship with Native American tribes, including investments in tribal nations, protection of sacred sites, and advancements in healthcare. He also criticized former President Trump and expressed concern about the future of American democracy. President Biden urged unity and called on Democrats, Republicans, and independents to come together for the upcoming election, which he deemed as one of the most critical in modern history.